com.latencybusters.lbmct

Interface LbmCtRcvConnDeleteCallback


  • public interface LbmCtRcvConnDeleteCallback
    Callback interface to deliver the "connection deleted" event to a receiving application. The application supplies an implementation of this interface to LbmCtRcv.start(com.latencybusters.lbmct.LbmCt, java.lang.String, com.latencybusters.lbm.LBMReceiverAttributes, com.latencybusters.lbm.LBMReceiverCallback, com.latencybusters.lbmct.LbmCtRcvConnCreateCallback, com.latencybusters.lbmct.LbmCtRcvConnDeleteCallback, java.lang.Object).

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      void onRcvConnDelete(LbmCtRcv rcv, LbmCtPeerInfo peerInfo, java.lang.Object cbArg, java.lang.Object connCbArg)
      Receiver application callback method, called by CT, to indicate that a connection is deleted.

    • Method Detail

      • onRcvConnDelete

        void onRcvConnDelete(LbmCtRcv rcv,
                     LbmCtPeerInfo peerInfo,
                     java.lang.Object cbArg,
                     java.lang.Object connCbArg)
        Receiver application callback method, called by CT, to indicate that a connection is deleted.

        Parameters:
        rcv - The CT Receiver object, that the deleted connection applies to.
        peerInfo - Useful information about the connection, such as the metadata of the connected source.
        cbArg - Application-specific object supplied by the application to LbmCtRcv.start(com.latencybusters.lbmct.LbmCt, java.lang.String, com.latencybusters.lbm.LBMReceiverAttributes, com.latencybusters.lbm.LBMReceiverCallback, com.latencybusters.lbmct.LbmCtRcvConnCreateCallback, com.latencybusters.lbmct.LbmCtRcvConnDeleteCallback, java.lang.Object).
        connCbArg - Application-specific object associated with the connection, supplied by the application as the return value from LbmCtRcvConnCreateCallback.onRcvConnCreate(com.latencybusters.lbmct.LbmCtRcv, com.latencybusters.lbmct.LbmCtPeerInfo, java.lang.Object).
